entries.content: Prospect states, 'I'd love to work with you, I've just got to see if my boss will pay.'
entries.notes: Presented as a common statement indicating a potential obstacle or objection.

entries.content: Interpret 'I've just got to see if my boss will pay' as a lack of personal commitment from the prospect.
entries.notes: Speaker's view on the root cause of this statement, leading to disqualification rather than typical objection handling.

focus_area: Objection Discovery: Clarifying questions, isolation, root cause
